  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-fcf665cd-7fff-d3fd-3bec-4fb1af035d11&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;The proposed railings and rear screening, by virtue of their detailed design and siting, would result in incongruous and inharmonious additions to the host property that would be out of keeping with the pattern of development in the street and would fail to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the Northwold and Cazenove Conservation Area. Furthermore, the proposed alterations would fail to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;conserve or enhance and reveal the significance of the locally listed building and its setting. The proposal would, therefore, be &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;contrary to policies D1, D3, D4, and HC1 of the London Plan (2021) and policies LP1, LP3, and LP4 of the Hackney: A Place for Everyone – Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14.6667px; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;The proposed use of the roof as a terrace and associated screening could result in noise and disturbance, and direct overlooking that would have a significant adverse impact on the amenities of neighbouring occupiers contrary to policy D3 of the London Plan (2021) and policy LP2 of the Hackney: A Place for Everyone – Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
